# 3. Describe a Project Involving Multiple Teams

### Situation

"When we started building the enterprise validation platform at Wells Fargo, different teams were using different technologies and validation approaches."

### Task

"Our goal was to create a single validation ecosystem that could support all model types while satisfying governance and compliance requirements."

### Action

"I worked closely with:

* Model Development Teams
* Model Validation Teams
* Infrastructure Teams
* Data Engineering Teams
* Risk and Governance Teams

Each group had different priorities. Development teams wanted flexibility, validators wanted consistency, and governance teams wanted security and compliance.

I organized architecture reviews, collected requirements, identified common pain points, and proposed a wrapper-based architecture that standardized interactions across all frameworks."

### Result

"The platform became the enterprise standard for validating over 100 models annually and reduced validation cycle time from about three months to two weeks."

### One Microsoft Principle

"The biggest lesson was that success depended less on technology and more on aligning different teams around a common goal."

