# 8. Explain the Architecture

```text
+----------------------+
|    Validator Layer   |
|      (ValTest)       |
+----------+-----------+
           |
           |
        gRPC
           |
           v

+----------------------+
|  Transponder Client  |
+----------+-----------+
           |
    Apache Arrow
           |
           v

+----------------------+
|   Wrapped Models     |
|    (ValOps Layer)    |
+----------+-----------+
           |
-----------------------------------------
|      |       |      |      |          |
SAS  Sklearn  H2O  HF LLMs  RAG  Agents
```

### Components

### ValOps

Provides a standard interface for every framework.

Examples:

```python
predict()
predict_proba()
generate()
embed()
```

Every framework implements the same contract.

---

### Transponder

Handles secure communication between environments.

Responsibilities:

* Serialization
* Data transfer
* Security controls
* Environment isolation

---

### ValTest

Executes validation logic.

Examples:

* Hallucination testing
* Toxicity testing
* Groundedness
* Fairness
* OOD testing
* Adversarial testing

---

### Benefits

* Framework agnostic
* Reusable validation
* Enterprise compliant
* Scalable onboarding

